<br />Heh, I think I know what you mean. When I started my project, I used to plan everything very carefully, so everything looked nice. Now I just write the stuff directly into the code files, and I'll write whatever it takes to test my new ideas, even if the code is not very pretty.
<br />
<br />After I see that the ideas work fine, I rewrite the code, making it look better, adding comment and maybe even optimizing a little.

		

